      "body": "> Where in Autotools were we running checks to verify the existence of singlular boost headers at configure time?\r\n\r\nI haven't confirmed this, but I assumed it checked for `boost/version.hpp` existence (and version conformance). Though, maybe I am wrong. In any case, anything is fine by me. I just found that it would be nice if calling `rm -rf ./bld-cmake/ && cmake -B ./bld-cmake` was fast, so all developers can just call it every time, without having to think about it much.",
